{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# WS6 — Rewire the Gerrit review-bot to the four-pass code review\n\n## Why\nEpic `d251` (AWS Gerrit + rebar MCP) **shipped and merged** — including S4b's complete review-bot:\n`src/rebar/review_bot/` (receiver `app.py`, `voter.py`, `gerrit_client.py`, `dedup.py`,\n`reconcile.py`) plus the **verdict→label seam `adapter.code_review_decision(diff_text, repo_root,\nref) → {decision, message, findings}`**. That seam is currently implemented over the OLD\nsingle-pass `rebar.llm.review_code(...)` + a blocking-severity heuristic — a deliberate \"proven\npipe\" placeholder. `adapter.py`'s own docstring says: *\"b744-WS6 will REIMPLEMENT this same\nsignature over `gate_dispatch.produce_code_review_verdict` — drop-in, with no caller change.\"*\n\nWS6 is exactly that swap: make Gerrit's `LLM-Review` vote driven by **our new four-pass code\nreview** (the deterministic Pass-3 blocker), not the single-pass demo.\n\n## Realignment (2026-06-30) — supersedes the earlier standalone-package plan\nThe pre-merge WS6 plan (a NEW `src/rebar/gerrit/` voter package + REST client + patchset handler)\nis **retired as redundant**: d251 already ships all of that in `src/rebar/review_bot/`. WS6 must\nNOT build a parallel package — it CONSUMES the shipped receiver and swaps only the decision engine\nbehind the existing seam. The live dogfood is split out to WS6-b (`0da5`); the GitHub cutover to\nWS7.\n\n## What\n- **Rewrite `src/rebar/review_bot/adapter.py`'s `code_review_decision`** over\n  `gate_dispatch.produce_code_review_verdict` (the typed `PASS`/`BLOCK`/`INDETERMINATE` verdict):\n  - keep the signature + return shape (`{decision, message, findings}`, plus an additive\n    `coverage_gap` flag) so `voter.py` is unchanged;\n  - map the verdict fail-closed (below); the four-pass gate's own Pass-3 thresholds\n    (`criteria_routing.json`) decide PASS vs BLOCK, so the adapter no longer applies the\n    `blocking_severities` severity heuristic (it becomes vestigial for this path);\n  - review the receiver's cloned working tree by passing `repo_root` (the security detectors scan\n    the changed files there) + the fetched `diff_text`.\n- **Add an `enabled: bool | None = None` override to `produce_code_review_verdict`** so the adapter\n  can pass `enabled=True` (force-enable): the code-review gate is OFF by default\n  (`verify.enable_code_review`), but voter activation is itself the authoritative gate, so the\n  per-repo flag would otherwise leave every change with the inert disabled verdict. (ADR 0013.)\n- **Update `tests/unit/test_review_bot.py`** adapter tests to drive the four-pass verdict (mock\n  `produce_code_review_verdict`) instead of `review_code`.\n- **ADR 0013** records the seam reimplementation + the force-enable rationale + the fail-closed\n  vote mapping + the coverage-gap message distinction.\n\n## Vote mapping (fail-closed; the gate's Pass-3 owns PASS/BLOCK)\n`produce_code_review_verdict` emits three verdicts (PASS/BLOCK/INDETERMINATE) plus an inert\ndisabled verdict. The adapter collapses them to the receiver's PASS/BLOCK (the voter then casts\n`llm_review_max_value` / `llm_review_block_value` from `ReceiverConfig`):\n\n| verdict / state | adapter decision | note |\n|---|---|---|\n| PASS + full coverage | PASS | advisory findings are surfaced in the message, non-blocking |\n| BLOCK (blocking findings) | BLOCK | real finding (`coverage_gap=False`) |\n| INDETERMINATE (LLM outage) | BLOCK | fail-closed coverage-gap |\n| PASS but `coverage.enabled==false` (inert) | BLOCK | fail-closed coverage-gap (`gate-disabled`) — defense-in-depth |\n| fail-closed security-scanner abstain | BLOCK | fail-closed coverage-gap (`scanner`) |\n| ANY exception / bad shape | BLOCK | fail-closed coverage-gap (`review-error`) |\n\n## Distinct coverage-gap message (infra vs code)\nThe vote comment (`ReviewInput.message`, posted by the receiver's `post_vote`) begins with a\nmachine-parseable tag so an INFRA `-1` is unmistakable from a real-finding `-1`:\n`[LLM-Review: PASS]`, `[LLM-Review: BLOCK — finding]`, and\n`[LLM-Review: BLOCK — coverage-gap (<gate-disabled|llm-unavailable|scanner|review-error>)]`. The\n`coverage_gap` sub-reason is derived deterministically from `verdict.coverage`\n(`enabled==false` → gate-disabled; `llm_unavailable` → llm-unavailable; a `security_detectors`\nnote with `reason=='fail-closed-abstain'` → scanner). A real secret MATCH\n(`reason=='detector-finding'`) is a finding, NOT a coverage gap.\n\n## Scope\n- IN: the `adapter.py` reimplementation, the `produce_code_review_verdict` `enabled` override, the\n  updated `test_review_bot.py` adapter tests, ADR 0013.\n- OUT: the receiver/voter/gerrit_client/reconciler (d251 shipped them — unchanged); the live\n  end-to-end dogfood (WS6-b, gated on the deployed env); the GitHub cutover (WS7).\n\n## Dependencies\n- CONSUMES d251's shipped `review_bot` package + the provisioned `LLM-Review` label / value\n  mapping (`ReceiverConfig`). depends_on WS4 (98ff, closed) for `produce_code_review_verdict`.\n- No live env needed: the adapter is fully verifiable offline (mock the verdict; the receiver's\n  own tests already stub Gerrit).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `review_bot/adapter.py`'s `code_review_decision` is reimplemented over `produce_code_review_verdict` with `enabled=True`; the signature + `{decision, message, findings}` return shape are unchanged (the voter is not touched).\n- [ ] Vote mapping is exhaustive + fail-closed over PASS / BLOCK / INDETERMINATE / inert-disabled / scanner-abstain / exception; a test asserts each → the correct decision, and that an inert-disabled verdict never yields PASS.\n- [ ] `produce_code_review_verdict` gains an `enabled: bool | None = None` override (default None = read config); a test asserts `enabled=True` forces the gate to run even when `verify.enable_code_review=false`.\n- [ ] The vote message distinguishes a coverage-gap `-1` (sub-reason gate-disabled / llm-unavailable / scanner / review-error) from a real-finding `-1`, via the documented first-line tag; a test asserts the PASS tag, the finding tag, and each coverage-gap sub-reason.\n- [ ] `tests/unit/test_review_bot.py` adapter tests are updated to the four-pass verdict (mock `produce_code_review_verdict`); the full `pytest -k review_bot` suite passes; ruff + mypy clean.\n- [ ] ADR 0013 records the seam reimplementation, the force-enable rationale, the fail-closed vote mapping, and the coverage-gap message vocabulary.","title":"WS6: Rewire the Gerrit review-bot to the four-pass code review"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782868087491845001,"uuid":"4fe1a716-6b46-4dc1-97a5-55e3ae1753f2"}